sentences: Frédéric Adam (4 January 1904 – 7 September 1984) was a French conductor, composer and administrator.
He became a répétiteur at the opera house in Strasbourg in 1933, remaining there until his retirement in 1972, including periods as co-director from 1955 to 1960 and director from 1960 to 1972.
